---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Manifesto | Jamal Williams">
	<section class="space-y-12 py-20 animate-fade-in">
		<header class="space-y-4">
			<a href="/" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-white transition-colors flex items-center gap-2 mb-8">
				<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" /></svg>
				Back Home
			</a>
			<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-7xl font-display animate-slide-up">
				The Generalist <span class="text-gradient">Manifesto</span>
			</h1>
		</header>

		<div class="glass p-8 md:p-12 rounded-3xl space-y-8 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-lg animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.1s;">
			<p class="text-xl font-medium text-white italic border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6 py-2">
				"As far as I can remember, I have never wanted to be the best at anything. Better than a particular friend or rival, sure, but never THE best. The world is full of fun, interesting things."
			</p>

			<div class="space-y-6">
				<p>
					My mother once described my father as a <strong>Renaissance man</strong>. When she explained what that meant, my path was set. I am an unapologetic generalist.
				</p>
				<p>
					In a world that demands hyper-specialization, I choose the margins. I choose the intersection. Hyper-specialization is a waste of time and, more importantly, incredibly boring. Why give up new experiences to focus on doing the same thing over and over?
				</p>
				<p>
					My approach is simple: If it's interesting, I'll learn more. If I don't hate it, I'll try to be decent. If I love it, I might get really good. 
				</p>
				<p>
					Decent is the floor. Excellence is the practice. Freedom is the goal.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 pt-8 border-t border-slate-800">
				<div class="space-y-4">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white font-display">I make physical crafts.</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-400">Working with my hands to shape the tangible world.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="space-y-4">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white font-display">I make digital creations.</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-400">Architecting systems and code that empower narratives.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="space-y-4">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white font-display">I shape businesses.</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-400">Consulting that prioritizes freedom and integrity.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="space-y-4">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white font-display">I build developers.</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-400">Leadership and mentorship to elevate the craft.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<p class="text-white font-semibold pt-8">
				It's a wide range of skills, but it all boils down to this: I make things better.
			</p>
		</div>

		<footer class="pt-12 flex justify-between">
			<a href="/principles" class="btn-primary">View Principles</a>
		</footer>
	</section>
</Layout>
